data.name: Dark Electrode
rules: This Pokémon is both Lightning Darkness type.

abilities.name: Darkness Navigation
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Dark Electrode has no Energy attached to it, you may search your deck for a Darkness or Dark Metal Energy and attach it to Dark Electrode. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Dark Electrode is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Energy Bomb
attacks.text: You may move all Energy cards attached to Dark Electrode to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like.

abilities.name: Super Dynamo
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Electrode is your Active Pokémon, you may flip a coin. If heads, choose a Lightning Energy card from your discard pile and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. This power can't be used if Electrode is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Swift
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

data.name: Electrode

attacks.name: Chain Lightning
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon isn't Colorless, this attack does 10 damage to each Benched Pokémon of the same type as the Defending Pokémon (including your own).

data.flavorText: It stores electrical energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.

attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Mass Destruction
attacks.text: Both Electrode and the Defending Pokémon are now Knocked Out. If Electrode has any Special Energy cards attached to it, this attack does nothing.

data.name: Holon's Electrode
rules: You may attach this as an Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon that already has an Energy card attached to it. When you attach this card, return an Energy card attached to that Pokémon to your hand. While attached, this card is a Special Energy card and provides every type of Energy but 2 Energy at a time. (Has no effect other than providing Energy.)

attacks.name: Dazzle Blast
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Electroblast
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of "The Bomb Ball."

abilities.name: Buzzap
abilities.text: At any time during your turn (before your attack), you may Knock Out Electrode and attach it to 1 of your other Pokémon. If you do, choose a type of Energy. Electrode is now an Energy card (instead of a Pokémon) that provides 2 energy of that type. You can't use this power if Electrode is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Electric Shock

data.flavorText: It stores electrical energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.

abilities.name: Energy Shift

(Has no effect other than providing Energy.)
